          "date": "2013-10-18 08:42:20.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-4053 hsm: Don't acquire layout lock on dirty flush",
        "message": "LU-4053 hsm: Don't acquire layout lock on dirty flush\n\nIt's not necessary to acquire layout lock on flush dirty.\n\nThis patch reverted the change of LU-3160:\n(3141db609d95d379761e3b54899618b4037d38f6) where we disabled\n'ignore_layout' for dirty flush to avoid the race of writeback\nvs. layout changing. Actually, such race can be avoided by\nfixing the lov_io_init() to always get conf lock regardless\nof the 'ignore_layout' flag.\n\nTest-Parameters: envdefinitions=DURATION=7200 \\\nclientdistro=el6 serverdistro=el6 clientcount=4 \\\nosscount=2 mdscount=2 austeroptions=-R failover=true \\\nuseiscsi=true testlist=recovery-random-scale\n\nSigned-off-by: Niu Yawei <yawei.niu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Id6a0567a6bb7cd0176bff6341d1932cc8f9e7c99\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
